gw.plugin.assignment

Class AssignmentResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.plugin.assignment.AssignmentResponse
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GWRemotable

    public final class AssignmentResponse
extends java.lang.Object
implements GWRemotable
    AssignmentResponse represents the information that an implementation of IAssignmentAdapter must return. The implementation is based on the Command design pattern: member values define a specific execution within ClaimCenter.

      • isReviewAssignment

        public boolean isReviewAssignment()
        Whether or not the assignment is to be reviewed. If so, a review activity will be created and associated with the item being assigned. See the documentation associated with reviewerID below for an understanding of how the activity will be assigned.

        Ignored if assignmentCommand is one of:

        1. ASSIGN_MANUALLY
        2. ASSIGN_NOT_FOUND

      • setReviewAssignment

        public void setReviewAssignment(boolean reviewAssignment)
        Whether or not the assignment is to be reviewed. If so, a review activity will be created and associated with the item being assigned. See the documentation associated with reviewerID below for an understanding of how the activity will be assigned.

        Ignored if assignmentCommand is one of:

        1. ASSIGN_MANUALLY
        2. ASSIGN_NOT_FOUND

      • getReviewerId

        public java.lang.String getReviewerId()
        An optional value specifying the person that the review activity will be assigned to. If this value is set then the person identified will be assigned the activity. In terms of the group, if the person exists in the same group as the basis (non-review) item, then the activity will be assigned in terms of that group. Otherwise, the first group the reviewer is in will be used for the assignment.

        If this value is not specified, then the review activity will be assigned to the supervisor of the group that the basis item is assigned to.

      • setReviewerId

        public void setReviewerId(java.lang.String reviewerId)
        An optional value specifying the person that the review activity will be assigned to. If this value is set then the person identified will be assigned the activity. In terms of the group, if the person exists in the same group as the basis (non-review) item, then the activity will be assigned in terms of that group. Otherwise, the first group the reviewer is in will be used for the assignment.

        If this value is not specified, then the review activity will be assigned to the supervisor of the group that the basis item is assigned to.

        public java.lang.String getGroupID()

        Required if assignmentCommand is one of:

        Ignored if assignmentCommand is one of:

        3. ASSIGN_NOT_FOUND
